# metis base.manifest — metis's module declaration for the weave layer compiler.
#
# metis is the ML-workbench SUBSTRATE layer: it consumes ariadne (construct/deps
# `substrate ../ariadne`) and is itself consumed by kaggle. It inherits ariadne's
# EXPORTED base layer through that edge, and will EXPORT its own ML tooling
# (the experiment datatype, the step-runner, the metis step-types) downstream via
# `export` rows added as those land (kaggle-ml-base-layer, metis#1). For now it
# declares only its OWN internal constitution.
#
# Format and verbs: see ariadne's construct/base.manifest. The leading `internal`
# token (ariadne#99) keeps an artifact with this repo (selected only on its own
# self-walk); an ancestor's internal artifacts never leak DOWN into a consumer's
# composed AGENTS.md (the #95 fix). NOTE: shipping a base.manifest is ALSO what
# marks metis as a TRAVERSABLE layer — without it, a consumer's (kaggle's) weave
# walk stops at metis and never reaches ariadne.

# ── Constitution ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
internal  prose AGENTS.local.md
# Exported ML-workspace conventions: flows down to kaggle + kbench so a session
# started in any competition/research workspace folder reads that folder's
# README.md as the entry point ("continue" suffices).
export    prose AGENTS.ml.md

# ── Skills ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# metis authors its own ML-workbench skills under construct/local — weave scans
# each <name>/SKILL.md and lowers them to per-harness symlinks (.claude/skills for
# Claude, .agents/skills for Codex/Gemini). Bare (not `internal`) = EXPORT: they
# flow down the layer walk to kaggle + kbench, so rogii-v2 inherits `ml-research`.
# First skill: ml-research (the ml-research-workflow project's A1).
skill     construct/local
